{"first_name":"Tony","last_name":"Perkins","permalink":"tony-perkins","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/tony-perkins","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"TonyPerkins","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"GoingOn","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Fri Jul 20 04:57:34 UTC 2007","updated_at":"Thu Aug 06 23:51:29 UTC 2009","overview":"<p>Tony Perkins is a Venture Partner with DFJ Frontier. He is the creator and former editor-in-chief of Red Herring magazine and the CEO of AlwaysOn, an interactive online network for technology insiders. Perkins co-authored &#8220;The Internet Bubble: Inside the Overvalued World of High-Tech Stocks&#8221;, a book that foretold the dot-com bust.</p>\n\n<p>Perkins served on President George W. Bush&#8217;s Information Technology Advisory Council and he was the founding chairman of the Churchill Club in Palo Alto, California, for which he received the Ernst &amp; Young Entrepreneur of the Year Award. </p>\n\n<p>He has been a member of the World Economic Forum&#8217;s Media Leaders group since 1996. Perkins was also founder and CEO of Upside Publishing and Vice President of Business Development at Silicon Valley Bank. </p>\n\n<p>Perkins continues to chronicle the technology world in a regular column for the Wall Street Journal and as television commentator for MSNBC&#8217;s Hardball with Chris Matthews, CNN, CNBC, BBC, and Bloomberg Television. </p>\n\n<p>Tony Perkins graduated from UC Davis with a BA in Western European History/Political Science.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[118,150],"assets/images/resized/0004/4876/44876v1-max-150x150.jpg"],[[198,250],"assets/images/resized/0004/4876/44876v1-max-250x250.jpg"],[[356,450],"assets/images/resized/0004/4876/44876v1-max-450x450.jpg"]],"attribution":"<p>Tony Perkins</p>"},"degrees":[{"degree_type":"B.A.","subject":"Western European History/Political Science","institution":"UC Dav